The paper discusses the dissemination time of a random linear network coding (RLNC) protocol in ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to network information theory (cs.IT) and network science (cs.SI). The focus on dynamic topology and the use of RLNC for broadcast dissemination suggest a connection to networked systems (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of probability mass functions and geometric random variables also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
